name: "Bill's Car" by Richard F. Yates (Holy Fool)
description:
[Liner pen on notebook page with some digital embellishments.]

Maybe he WAS busy that day, but was it right for Bill to just drive right on by? (It's actually a good thing he did---cuz the creature that did THIS to Phil was still nearby and would have happily pounced on an human that tried to help the guy quickly expiring on the sidewalk...) ---Richard F. Yates (Holy Fool)
